**Segments**

- By Product (Magnetostrictive, Piezoelectric, Sonic)
- By Modality (Standalone, Portable)
- By End-User (Hospitals, Dental Clinics, Ambulatory Surgical Centers)

The global dental scaling units market is segmented based on product, modality, and end-user. In terms of product, the market can be categorized into magnetostrictive, piezoelectric, and sonic scaling units. Magnetostrictive scaling units operate by converting electrical energy into mechanical vibrations, while piezoelectric scaling units use crystals to generate ultrasonic vibrations for scaling. Sonic scaling units produce vibrations through compressed air, suitable for more delicate procedures. When it comes to modality, dental scaling units are available as standalone units for fixed setups or portable units for mobility and convenience. As for end-users, the market caters to hospitals, dental clinics, and ambulatory surgical centers, each with specific requirements and preferences in scaling unit functionalities.

